8":"1378","1454":"1454","31 January 1375":"31 januari 1375","1376":"1376","1343":"1343","1375":"1375","20 February 1348":"20 februari 1348","1408":"1408","1428":"1428","Avignon, Jura, Franche-Comté, France":"Avignon, Jura, Franche-Comté, Frankrijk","Ruthven, Perthshire, Scotland":"Ruthven, Perthshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Perth, , Perthshire, Scotland":"Perth, Perthshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1357–1376":"1357–1376","1351–Male":"1351–Deceased","1343–1408":"1343–1408","1360–1428":"1360–1428","1378–Male":"1378–Deceased","1379–1454":"1379–1454","1324–1363":"1324–1363","1325–1375":"1325–1375","1363":"1363","1351":"1351","1360":"1360","Abt 1360":"about 1360","1325":"1325","1357":"1357","Bef 1370":"before 1370","1324":"1324","1379":"1379","1378":"1378","1454":"1454","31 January 1375":"31 January 1375","1376":"1376","1343":"1343","1375":"1375","20 February 1348":"20 February 1348","1408":"1408","1428":"1428","Avignon, Jura, Franche-Comté, France":"Avignon, Jura, Franche-Comté, France","Ruthven, Perthshire, Scotland":"Ruthven, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Perth, , Perthshire, Scotland":"Perth, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Logie","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Eugenie.","Scottish: habitational name from any of various places so called, from Gaelic <i>lag</i> ‘hollow’ + the locative suffix <i>-ach</i>.","French (mainly Nord; <b>Logié</b>) and Flemish: variant of <b>Logier</b>, from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Hlodgari</i> (Latinized as <i>Lodegarius</i>), composed of the elements <i>hlōd</i> ‘famous’ and <i>gari</i> (from <i>garwa</i>) ‘ready, eager’ or <i>gari</i> ‘spear’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margaret Logie was born in 1357, in Perth, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, her father, Sir John Erskine Logie of that Ilk, was 33 and her mother, Margaret Drummond Queen Consort of Scotland, was 32. She married William Ruthven Laird of Ruthven before 1370. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died in 1376, in her hometown, at the age of 19."},"et":{"1357–1376":"1357–1376","1351–Male":"1351–Surnud","1343–1408":"1343–1408","1360–1428":"1360–1428","1378–Male":"1378–Surnud","1379–1454":"1379–1454","1324–1363":"1324–1363","1325–1375":"1325–1375","1363":"1363","1351":"1351","1360":"1360","Abt 1360":"umbes 1360","1325":"1325","1357":"1357","Bef 1370":"enne 1370","1324":"1324","1379":"1379","1378":"1378","1454":"1454","31 January 1375":"31. jaanuar 1375","1376":"1376","1343":"1343","1375":"1375","20 February 1348":"20. veebruar 1348","1408":"1408","1428":"1428","Avignon, Jura, Franche-Comté, France":"Avignon, Jura, Franche-Comté, Prantsusmaa","Ruthven, Perthshire, Scotland":"Ruthven, Perthshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Perth, , Perthshire, Scotland":"Perth, Perthshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1357–1376":"1357–1376","1351–Male":"1351–Kuollut","1343–1408":"1343–1408","1360–1428":"1360–1428","1378–Male":"1378–Kuollut","1379–1454":"1379–1454","1324–1363":"1324–1363","1325–1375":"1325–1375","1363":"1363","1351":"1351","1360":"1360","Abt 1360":"noin 1360","1325":"1325","1357":"1357","Bef 1370":"ennen vuotta 1370","1324":"1324","1379":"1379","1378":"1378","1454":"1454","31 January 1375":"31. tammikuuta 1375","1376":"1376","1343":"1343","1375":"1375","20 February 1348":"20. helmikuuta 1348","1408":"1408","1428":"1428","Avignon, Jura, Franche-Comté, France":"Avignon, Jura, Franche-Comté, Ranska","Ruthven, Perthshire, Scotland":"Ruthven, Perthshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Perth, , Perthshire, Sc